  "What does 'activated complex' mean?": "",
  "A molecule that activates a catalyst": "",
  "The reactant with the highest energy": "",
  "A stable intermediate product": "",
  "The temporary, high-energy species formed at the transition state of a reaction": "",
  "The activated complex is the unstable, high-energy species that forms at the peak of the energy profile (transition state) during the conversion of reactants to products.": "",
